ZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
As for this girl in particular you mentioned...<br>
Note: I'm making some assumptions here based on the limited info that you gave us.<br>
<br>
You haven't spoken in 3 months but you're in the same class?  If you're waiting on a shy girl to make a move, you will be waiting your entire life.  She probably feels bad for having to tell you she couldn't see you because she was sick and thinks that you think she's not interested in you and has already put a stake in the whole affair and is scared shitless to talk to you because she figures you hate her now.  <br>
<br>
Ok, that was convoluted...but we're talking chicks here...  In fact, because you've already waited 3 fucking months, she's probably certain that's the case.  If I were you I would start talking to her again.  Take it slow and let her get comfortable with you.  Keep things light and let her know (after you think she's comfortable again) that you'd like to still go out with her. She will probably say yes. <br>
<br>
Oh, you need something to say to her...<br>
Bring up shit you have in common (if you know of anything), ask her how she's doing, make observations (always a good one especially if they are humorous), discuss current events/acitivities, etc.  If she mentions her illness, you can relate your experience contracting Herpes Simplex X, etc.  A good sense of humor works wonders to break the ice.<br>
<br>
Final note: I don't claim to be an expert on women. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Most of these things just come naturally after a while with experience. <p>Bethude -Triton-
